		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} backs a daring plan to explore the far corners of the globe!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_CHOICE_5_S">
			<Text>{1_CivShortDescription}'s Reforms the Economy</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} seizes the aristocracy's remaining power in a move to reform Portugal's economy!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_CHOICE_6_S">
			<Text>{1_CivShortDescription}'s Colonial Naturalization</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} naturalizes all her citizens, finalising decades of social reform!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_DESCRIPTION">
			<Text>Mother Of Wisdom</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_HELP">
			<Text>Your Most Faithful Majesty, we must report the rather worrying behavior of the Marquis of Pombal as of late. Though in the past he has proved an ally to the throne, I fear for his current intentions.[NEWLINE]Perhaps the Queen would consider an extended vacation until we can resolve the matter?</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_HELP_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>Receive a Great Person of your choice.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_HELP_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>{2_InstantYield} emigrate to set up colonies abroad. The infrastructure of their travel permenantly increases [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production of Sea Units by 15%, and [ICON_CONNECTED] City Connections provide 2% additional [ICON_GOLD] Gold for every City.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_HELP_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>Call upon {1_YieldCost} of religious fervour to defeat your foes. Your Cities produce {3_CityYield}. All Melee and Gun Units receive the Stalwart Promotion.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_HELP_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>Pour {1_YieldCost} into an Age of Discovery. An Explorer appears near every City. Enter a [ICON_GOLDEN_AGE] Golden Age for 10 Turns. Existing Scouting Units (as well as those produced in this time) receive the Scouting 3 Promotion.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_HELP_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>Reform the domestic economy, entering 2 Turns of Anarchy. Receive 2 copies of [ICON_RES_WINE] Wine. Every Town, Village, and Feitoria yields +1 [ICON_GOLD] Gold and +1 [ICON_FOOD] Food.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_HELP_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>Naturalisation of colonials causes Harbours to yield +1 [ICON_GOLD] Gold, [ICON_FOOD] Food and [ICON_GOLDEN_AGE] Golden Age Point per turn for every City you own. However, the many languages, practices and prejudices brought into contact by the free movement of people increases [ICON_GOLD] Poverty and [ICON_RESEARCH] Illiteracy thresholds by 10%.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>I will not flee before some second-rate statesman! We shall simply appoint a new marquis, it's not as if the position is cursed! Off with his head!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>*An important ethnic group are semi-nomadic, at this time they are looking to move to their next home*[NEWLINE]The Vandal ships are sitting in the Harbour, ready to depart. See to it that the Marquis wakes up on one.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>*Many of the nobles doubt our ability, as a woman, to win this war. It is no surprise they are considering a replacement*[NEWLINE]By my divine right, I shall pray for a sign from God! When all Portugal see that I fight for His justice, they will rally behind me to defeat these foreign devils!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>*The Marquis's principle enemy at court is constantly petitioning the crown for men and money for crazed voyages beyond the horizon*[NEWLINE]This 'navigator' chap seeks to do the impossible. Very well, if we put him in charge the ensuing chaos will surely take the wind out of the Marquis's sails.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_PORTUGAL_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_5">
